We recommend that the PAPs of Municipality Disaster Risk Reduction and Management Office strengthen its capabilities to enable it to perform its mandated functions under Section 4, Rule 6, IRR of R.A. 10121, and COA Circular No. 2012-002 specifically with the regards to the following:
1. Formulate and implement a comprehensive and integrated LDRRMP in accordance with the national, regional and provincial framework and policies on disaster risk reduction and management in coordination with the local development councils (LDC);
2. Prepare and submit to the Local Sanggunian, through Local Disaster Risk Reduction and Management Council (LDRRMC) and the LDC, the annual LDRRMO plan and budget, the proposed programming of the LDRRMF, other dedicated disaster risk reduction and management resources;
3. Prepare LDRRMFIP for the DRRM program annually according to the guidelines and format required under COA Circular No. 2012-002.
We also recommend that the LDRRMO submit explanation / justification on the low utilization of the LDRRMF specifically those which pertains to the 70% allocation for preparation and mitigation.

observations.managementAction:
Follow COA Recommendation. Validation on the compliance by the Management revealed the following were not indicated in the trip tickets.
1. Name of passengers;
2. Places to be visited/inspected.
3. Purpose/s of the trip;
4. Name and signatures of passenger/s
5. Date of Travel;
6. Almost all the figures on Gasoline/Diesel line issued, purchased and consumed with alterations;
7. Monthly report of official travels were not supported with trip tickets in each vehicle. Trip tickets are filed separately and submitted to the auditor only upon demand by the auditor.

